results.name: Decimal expansion of real part of the infinite power tower of i.
comment: This is the real part of i^i^i^i^i^i...
link: Eric Weisstein's World of Mathematics, Power Tower
formula: The value is 2 (i/Pi) W(-i Pi/2) = 0.4382829... + i 0.360592..., where W denotes the principal branch of the Lambert W function. - David W. Cantrell, Nov 23 2007
